// @test regression/INV051-method-as-variable
// @description `method` is a contextual keyword. When used as a plain variable name (assignment, comparison, indexing, member access) it must NOT be parsed as a method declaration. TV accepts all of these; we previously emitted a phantom "Expected method name after 'method'". See investigations/INV051-method-contextual-keyword/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects no-errors
//@version=6
indicator("t")
method = input.string("ADX", options = ["ADX", "Volatility"])
other = method == "ADX" ? 1 : 2
plot(close, color = method == "ADX" ? color.red : color.blue)
plot(other)
